<h1>THIS PAGE IS NOW DEPRECATED, PLEASE DO NOT REFERENCE UNLESS YOU ARE A DEVELOPER</h1>

<p>
  Outpost funds your hardware build. When you start a project as
  <strong>"I need Funding"</strong>, log your design hours, then hit
  <strong>"Submit Design to Get Project Funding"</strong> and pick the complexity
  tier that matches what you're making. A reviewer approves a grant up to that
  tier's maximum.
</p>

<h2>The tiers</h2>
<div class="tier-guide">
  <% Certification::FundingRequest::TIERS.each do |_id, t| %>
    <div class="tier-guide__row">
      <span class="funding-tier__badge funding-tier__badge--<%= t[:code].downcase %>"><%= t[:code] %></span>
      <div class="tier-guide__body">
        <div class="tier-guide__name"><%= t[:name] %></div>
        <div><%= t[:examples] %></div>
      </div>
      <span class="tier-guide__max">up to $<%= t[:max_cents] / 100 %></span>
    </div>
  <% end %>
</div>
<p>
  Got a build with a cool twist and real polish? Reviewers can bump it up a tier.
</p>

<h2>Spend less, earn Stardust</h2>
<p>
  You don't have to request your whole tier. For every dollar you leave on the
  table, you earn <strong><%= Certification::FundingRequest::DISCOUNT_STARDUST_PER_DOLLAR %> Stardust</strong>
  toward the <strong>Outpost Ticket</strong> in the shop. Once your accrued
  discount covers the ticket, the extra rolls into a <strong>flight stipend</strong>.
</p>

<h2>After your grant</h2>
<p>
  When your grant is approved, your project moves to the build stage. Log your
  build time with a timelapse and post at least one build devlog before you can
  ship. Only build-stage hours (after reviewer checks) earn Stardust at the
  voting booth. Design-stage hours don't pay out.
</p>
